# Shortcodes

- Every shortcode gets its own folder: `layouts/_shortcodes/{name}/{file}.html` — never a
  flat file directly under `layouts/_shortcodes/`. (Hugo renamed
  `layouts/shortcodes/` to `layouts/_shortcodes/` in v0.146.0; Phase 8 caught and
  migrated this — see `docs/RESEARCH.md` for the version history.)
- The Infobox shortcode family (`infobox`, `infobox-row`, `infobox-image`,
  `infobox-section`) must remain authorable **inline in the Markdown body** using nested
  paired/single shortcodes — never require front matter or a `data/*.yaml` file to define
  infobox content. This is a hard product requirement, not a style preference.
- Keep the four Infobox files each single-purpose: the outer wrapper renders the header
  and `.Inner`; each inner shortcode renders exactly one row/image/section-header
  concept. If new fields are needed, add a new inner shortcode file rather than growing
  an existing one with conditional branches.
- Class names emitted by shortcode templates (`infobox`, `infobox-header`,
  `infobox-row`, `infobox-label`, `infobox-data`, `infobox-image`, `infobox-caption`,
  `infobox-section-header`) must exactly match what `assets/css/components/infobox.scss`
  styles — treat the shortcode templates as the source of truth for these names.
- Values passed through shortcode params that may contain formatting (e.g. `value` on
  `infobox-row`) should render through `markdownify` to support inline bold/italic/links,
  consistent with how the value would look in real wikitext.
- Any new shortcode's usage must be documented in `docs/SHORTCODES.md` with a full
  worked example before being considered done.
